  "body": "\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: after chat screen is opened input filed overlaps with last message, so message is half-visible. After  this last message \"jumps up\", so it's fully visible. It happens in each chat type.\r\n\r\n\r\nwhen chat opened:\r\n![Screenshot_20190710-173857](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/60985641-18bf4980-a33e-11e9-9370-3628a1cbea6d.png)\r\n\r\na second later after chat is opened\r\n![Screenshot_20190710-173907](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/60985655-1eb52a80-a33e-11e9-9bca-0d09a1cc6147.png)\r\n\r\n![jump](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/60985815-7a7fb380-a33e-11e9-96db-235899038e9d.gif)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n\r\nChat screen shows all messages and nothing is moving on the screen if no new messages received\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nlast message jumps up after chat screen is opened\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- join public chat with message and open it\r\n- look at last message in the chat and if it moves on the  screen \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n- Status version: nightly july 10\r\n- Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n",
